summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of US automobile brands, detailing their market penetration and buyer defection rates. Brands like Pontiac and Dodge exhibit the highest market penetration at 9% and 8% respectively, with Pontiac showing a 58% buyer defection rate and Dodge also at 58%. Chevrolet and Ford, both at 8% and 6% market penetration, respectively, demonstrate higher buyer defection rates of 71%. Buick and Toyota, with 7% and 6% market penetration, show defection rates of 59% and 70%. Lower market penetration is seen with Oldsmobile and Mercury at 5% each, accompanied by high defection rates of 66% and 72%. Honda has the lowest market penetration at 4% but a high defection rate of 71%. The average buyer defection rate across these brands is 67%.
